Vera Sisson https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vera_Sisson 0 Vera Sisson (July 31, 1891 – August 6, 1954) was an American actress of the silent era. She appeared in 79 films between 1913 and 1926. She was born in Salt Lake City, Utah Territory and died in Carmel, California from a barbiturate overdose. Vera_Sisson ( July_31_,_1891 – August_6_,_1954 ) was an_American_actress of the_silent_era .
